radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is retrocecal location, dilated to 9 mm, fluid-filled, with thickened and hyperemic walls. Mild adjacent fat stranding. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are within normal limits. No focal lesions or abnormalities noted in the abdominal and pelvic areas. Prominent right lower quadrant ileocolonic lymph nodes are likely reactive.
